option.END_EVENT_SPOTLIGHT_ENABLED.comment=Theatre-style spotlight shines down from the cosmic eye onto the player when it opens. Follows the player, blinks with the eye, fades when it closes.

option.END_EVENT_SPOTLIGHT_RADIUS=Spotlight Radius
option.END_EVENT_SPOTLIGHT_RADIUS.comment=Half-width of the spotlight beam in blocks. Default 3.5 = a 7x7 block area. Controls both ground illumination and the volumetric light beam width.

option.END_EVENT_SPOTLIGHT_INTENSITY=Spotlight Intensity
option.END_EVENT_SPOTLIGHT_INTENSITY.comment=How bright the spotlight is. Higher values make the illuminated area more visible against the dark End terrain.

# ============================================================================
#   9. COMPATIBILITY
# ============================================================================

screen.COMPATIBILITY=Compatibility
screen.COMPATIBILITY.comment=World offset adjustments and LOD mod compatibility settings.

option.SEA_LEVEL_OFFSET=Sea Level Offset
option.SEA_LEVEL_OFFSET.comment=Offsets fog/cloud heights without moving terrain. Useful for custom world heights.

screen.DISTANT_HORIZONS=Distant Horizons
screen.DISTANT_HORIZONS.comment=Settings for the Distant Horizons mod (LOD chunks beyond normal render distance).

screen.VOXY=Voxy
screen.VOXY.comment=Settings for the Voxy LOD renderer.

option.DH_BRIGHTNESS=DH Brightness
option.DH_BRIGHTNESS.comment=Brightness multiplier for Distant Horizons terrain. Adjust to match vanilla chunk brightness.

option.DH_GRASS_BRIGHTNESS=DH Grass Brightness
option.DH_GRASS_BRIGHTNESS.comment=Brightness multiplier for grass blocks on DH LODs only. DH grass uses biome-baked colors that tend to read darker than chunk grass — tune this to match nearby chunk terrain.

option.DH_LEAF_BRIGHTNESS=DH Leaf Brightness
option.DH_LEAF_BRIGHTNESS.comment=Brightness multiplier for leaf blocks on DH LODs only. Tune to match nearby chunk foliage.

option.VOXY_LOD_BRIGHTNESS=Voxy LOD Brightness
option.VOXY_LOD_BRIGHTNESS.comment=Brightness multiplier for Voxy LOD terrain only. Fine 0.01-step control to match nearby chunk brightness precisely.

option.VOXY_SKY_TINT_BOOST=Sky Tint Boost
option.VOXY_SKY_TINT_BOOST.comment=Scales the warm/cool sky-color tint applied to LOD terrain. 1.0 = same tint strength as chunks, higher = more tinted. Raise if LODs look less sky-tinted than nearby chunks.

option.VOXY_SHADOW_OPACITY=Face Shading
option.VOXY_SHADOW_OPACITY.comment=Controls the contrast between lit and shaded faces on Voxy LOD blocks. 0 = flat/uniform brightness, 1 = default shading, higher = exaggerated contrast.

option.VOXY_SSS_ENABLED=Screen Space Shadows
option.VOXY_SSS_ENABLED.comment=Projects sun shadows from chunk geometry onto Voxy LOD terrain via a screen-space depth raymarch. Disable to skip the SSS pass on LOD pixels (small perf win).

option.VOXY_LEAF_BRIGHTNESS=Leaf Brightness
option.VOXY_LEAF_BRIGHTNESS.comment=Brightness multiplier for leaf blocks on Voxy LODs. Reduce to darken bright leaves.

screen.OAK_LEAF_FACES=Oak Leaf Faces
screen.OAK_LEAF_FACES.comment=Per-face brightness tuning for oak leaves on Voxy LODs. Adjust each face independently to get uniform appearance. Disable if using a resource pack that changes leaf textures.

option.VOXY_OAK_LEAF_FACES=Enable Face Tweaks
option.VOXY_OAK_LEAF_FACES.comment=Enables per-face brightness adjustment for oak leaves on Voxy LODs. Turn off if a resource pack changes oak leaf textures and the tweaks no longer match.

option.VOXY_OAK_LEAF_TOP=Top
option.VOXY_OAK_LEAF_TOP.comment=Brightness multiplier for the top face (UP) of oak leaf blocks. Stacks with Leaf Brightness.

option.VOXY_OAK_LEAF_BOTTOM=Bottom
option.VOXY_OAK_LEAF_BOTTOM.comment=Brightness multiplier for the bottom face (DOWN) of oak leaf blocks. Stacks with Leaf Brightness.

option.VOXY_OAK_LEAF_NORTH=North
option.VOXY_OAK_LEAF_NORTH.comment=Brightness multiplier for the north face of oak leaf blocks. Stacks with Leaf Brightness.

option.VOXY_OAK_LEAF_SOUTH=South
option.VOXY_OAK_LEAF_SOUTH.comment=Brightness multiplier for the south face of oak leaf blocks. Stacks with Leaf Brightness.

option.VOXY_OAK_LEAF_WEST=West
option.VOXY_OAK_LEAF_WEST.comment=Brightness multiplier for the west face of oak leaf blocks. Stacks with Leaf Brightness.

option.VOXY_OAK_LEAF_EAST=East
option.VOXY_OAK_LEAF_EAST.comment=Brightness multiplier for the east face of oak leaf blocks. Stacks with Leaf Brightness.

option.VOXY_GRASS_BRIGHTNESS=Grass Brightness
option.VOXY_GRASS_BRIGHTNESS.comment=Brightness multiplier for grass blocks on Voxy LODs. Fine 0.02-step increments for precise matching with nearby chunks.

option.VOXY_NIGHT_BRIGHTNESS=Night Brightness
option.VOXY_NIGHT_BRIGHTNESS.comment=Controls how bright Voxy LODs are at night. Higher = brighter nighttime terrain. 0 = no night ambient.

option.VOXY_HIGHLIGHT_COMPRESS=Highlight Compress
option.VOXY_HIGHLIGHT_COMPRESS.comment=Compresses bright colors to prevent snow, stone, and other light blocks from blowing out. 0 = off, higher = stronger. Use with higher LOD Brightness to lift darks without clipping brights.

option.VOXY_LOD_OUTLINES=LOD Outlines
option.VOXY_LOD_OUTLINES.comment=Enables cel-shading outlines on Voxy LOD terrain. Off by default since outlines on distant LODs can look noisy.

option.VOXY_TILE_BLUR_ENABLED=Face Flatten
option.VOXY_TILE_BLUR_ENABLED.comment=Flattens distant Voxy block faces to a single solid color. Reduces texture noise on far LODs. Ramps with distance.

option.VOXY_TILE_BLUR_START=Flatten Start
option.VOXY_TILE_BLUR_START.comment=Depth where face flattening begins. 0 = at camera, 0.85 = only distant LODs. Higher = more of the world keeps texture detail.

option.VOXY_CONTRAST=Contrast
option.VOXY_CONTRAST.comment=Contrast for Voxy LOD terrain. 1.0 = unchanged, higher = punchier darks and lights, lower = flatter.

option.VOXY_SATURATION=Saturation
option.VOXY_SATURATION.comment=Color saturation for Voxy LOD terrain. 0.0 = grayscale, 1.0 = unchanged, higher = oversaturated.

option.VOXY_EMISSIVE_INTENSITY=Emissive Intensity
option.VOXY_EMISSIVE_INTENSITY.comment=Emissive glow strength on Voxy LOD blocks. 0 = disabled, 1 = same as regular blocks.

option.VOXY_EMISSIVE_COLOR_STRENGTH=Emissive Color
option.VOXY_EMISSIVE_COLOR_STRENGTH.comment=How much emissive Voxy blocks keep their original color. 0 = white glow, 1 = full color.

option.VOXY_EMISSIVE_BRIGHTNESS_CAP=Emissive Cap
option.VOXY_EMISSIVE_BRIGHTNESS_CAP.comment=Maximum brightness for emissive Voxy blocks. Lower = less white blowout.

screen.CHUNK_FADE_OUT_SETTINGS=Chunk Fade Out Settings
screen.CHUNK_FADE_OUT_SETTINGS.comment=Settings for distance-based chunk fade around the player.
option.CHUNK_FADE_OUT_ENABLED=Chunk Fade Out
option.CHUNK_FADE_OUT_ENABLED.comment=Fades distant chunks out based on player radius.
option.CHUNK_FADE_OUT_RADIUS=Fade Radius
option.CHUNK_FADE_OUT_RADIUS.comment=Radius in blocks around the player where chunk fade begins.

option.DH_CONTRAST=DH Contrast
option.DH_CONTRAST.comment=Contrast for Distant Horizons LOD terrain. 1 = unchanged, higher = punchier darks and lights, lower = flatter.

option.DH_EMISSIVE_INTENSITY=DH Emissive Intensity
option.DH_EMISSIVE_INTENSITY.comment=Emissive glow strength on DH chunks. Makes lit areas visible at extreme distance.

option.DH_EMISSIVE_COLOR_STRENGTH=DH Emissive Color
option.DH_EMISSIVE_COLOR_STRENGTH.comment=How much emissive areas keep their original block color. 0 = white glow, 1 = full block color.

option.DH_EMISSIVE_BRIGHTNESS_CAP=DH Emissive Cap
option.DH_EMISSIVE_BRIGHTNESS_CAP.comment=Maximum brightness for emissive DH blocks. Prevents overly bright distant glowing areas.

option.DH_EMISSIVE_THRESHOLD=DH Emissive Threshold
option.DH_EMISSIVE_THRESHOLD.comment=Brightness level above which DH blocks are treated as emissive. Lower = more blocks glow.

option.DH_EMISSIVE_DEBUG=DH Emissive Debug
option.DH_EMISSIVE_DEBUG.comment=Highlights which DH blocks are detected as emissive. Use to fine-tune threshold.

option.DH_OVERDRAW_DISTANCE=Overdraw Distance
option.DH_OVERDRAW_DISTANCE.comment=Distance (blocks) where vanilla and DH chunks overlap. Prevents visible seam between vanilla and DH terrain.

option.DH_OVERDRAW_FADE_LENGTH=Overdraw Fade
option.DH_OVERDRAW_FADE_LENGTH.comment=Length of the crossfade zone between vanilla and DH terrain. Longer = smoother transition.
